author: arfrever
msg: Python 3 compatibility:
Update calls to print() in 'doc' directory.
* doc/tools/bin/find-xsl.py: Update calls to print().

author: gstein
msg: Followup to r35900: I missed a spot where the default DAV provider is
specified. This change makes serf the default.
* subversion/libsvn_ra/ra_loader.c:
(svn_ra_open3): change the default value when http-library is not
specified.

author: rhuijben
msg: * subversion/mod_dav_svn/util.c
(includes): Add http_protocol.h to fix compilation on Windows / Apache 2.2.

author: rhuijben
msg: * subversion/libsvn_subr/dirent_uri.c
(svn_uri_is_canonical): Update function to return false on UNC paths.
Code should use svn_dirent_*() (or svn_path_*()) on UNC paths.
* subversion/tests/libsvn_subr/dirent_uri-test.c
(test_dirent_is_canonical): Verify that canonical paths are not changed
by canonicalizing them.
(test_uri_is_canonical): Verify that canonical paths are not changed
by canonicalizing them. Add a few UNC path test values.

author: rhuijben
msg: * subversion/libsvn_subr/path.c
(svn_path_canonicalize, svn_path_is_canonical): Re-enable UNC path support
in these to be deprecated functions on Windows by routing UNC paths
to svn_dirent_*().
